devdoc.details: Secure storage for encrypted PII (SSN/IDs) using disposable pseudo-codes. This version includes a pay-to-access model and "Burn-on-Read" functionality.

businessRecall(uint256).details: Step 3: Business pays to access data. Logic: Release data -> Burn Token -> Collect Fee.

checkTokenStatus(uint256).details: Step 2: Public verification.  Businesses can check if a QR code/token is still valid before paying.

generateAndStore(bytes,uint256).details: Step 1: User/Admin stores the encrypted data. Takes an encrypted 'blob' and a desired number of disposable codes.

setAccessFee(uint256).details: Step 4: Monetization. Owner can change the access fee based on market value.
